        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 2:40PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 239 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Tuskegee, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tuskegee, Shorter, Franklin, Liverpool, Franklin Field, Lake
Tuskegee, Hardaway, Davisville, Warriorstand, Sedgefield, Fort Davis,
Cross Keys, and Uphapee Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
